Briefs = {
	"SWE": {
	"Software Engineer": "As Software Engineer you are involved with the entire development lifecycle, thus you analyse, design, propose, develop, test, configure, deploy, operate, troubleshoot, maintain, and improve multiple software products, services, pipelines and tools, and related components – which together compose an essential part of the service portfolio CSCS offers to the scientific community. You perform activities aimed at ensuring high quality and performant implementations and adherence to standards within the teams of work you are part of. You participate into planning and review activities. You collaborate with internal and external colleagues, scientists, and other stakeholders for the definition of the necessary architectures and roadmaps, for the necessary implementations and well as to communicate results.",
	"Data Engineer": "As Data Engineer you analyse, design, propose, model, develop, test, configure, deploy, operate, troubleshoot, maintain, and improve multiple data products, services, tools, ETL pipelines, and related components that are used to store, process, and analyse data – which together support the service portfolio that CSCS offers to the scientific community. You perform activities aimed at ensuring high quality and performant implementations and adherence to standards within your teams. You participate into planning and review activities. You collaborate with internal and external colleagues, scientists, and other stakeholders for the definition of the necessary architectures and roadmaps, for the necessary implementations and well as to communicate results.",
	"IAM Architect": "As IAM Architect you analyse, design, propose, develop, test, configure, deploy, operate, troubleshoot, maintain, and improve identity and access solutions, as well as related components and policies – which together are required to effectively serve the service portfolio that CSCS offers to the scientific community, as well as to facilitate the collaboration with partners. More broadly, you develop and maintain the vision and roadmap in the IAM field, in accordance with the current direction of the Centre.",
	"IT Security Analyst": "As IT Security Analyst you analyse, design, propose, develop, test, configure, deploy, operate, troubleshoot, maintain, and improve security related measures, components, services, monitoring, and tools aimed at protecting CSCS from cyber threats – which together reduce the likelihood of security alerts, incidents, and disasters – which would impact the scientific community served by CSCS. You handle security incidents, lead the end-to-end post-mortem processes, and write reports on adopted responses. You provide insights on the efficacy of the current security policies, controls and disaster recovery plans, and other security-related information.",
	"Information Security Officer": "As Information Security Officer you analyse, design, propose, establish, monitor, and maintain policies, procedures, and related measures – which together reduce the likelihood of to confidentiality, integrity, and availability incidents that would impact the scientific community served by CSCS. You educate employees about information security risks and best practices, as well as for improving compliance with policies and procedures. You conduct risk assessments to identify and mitigate potential vulnerabilities. In the event of a major security incident or if an important security topic arises, you are the interface between the management and the technical areas.",
	"Research Project Manager": "As Research Project Manager you plan, coordinate, and manage the research projects in which CSCS participates and involving internal and external stakeholders. You develop and monitor goals, plans, timelines, and costs for the fulfillment of commitments undertaken by CSCS. You contribute to the securing of fundings for the projects and you monitor that the resources available are allocated and effectively employed. You coordinate the required reporting production and communicate progress and results accordingly."
	},
    "RE" : {
    "Research Software Engineer": "As Research Software Engineer you collaborate with domain scientists to develop scientific applications and libraries able to leverage the most advanced supercomputers in the world, following best software engineering practices. As Research Software Engineer you are involved with the entire development lifecycle, thus you analyse, design, propose, develop, test, configure, deploy, operate, troubleshoot, maintain, and improve multiple software products, services, pipelines and tools, and related components – which together compose an essential part of the service portfolio CSCS offers to the scientific community. You perform activities aimed at ensuring high quality and performant implementations and adherence to standards within the teams of work you are part of. You participate into planning and review activities, collaborating with internal and external colleagues, scientists, and other stakeholders for the necessary implementations and well as to communicate results."
	},
	"SE": {
	"System Engineer": "As Systems Engineer you design, develop, deploy and operate a cutting edge HPC datacentre infrastructure in collaboration with industry leaders to support scientific research."
	},
	"HE": {
	"HPC Engineer": "As HPC Application Engineer you interface between CSCS' cutting-edge datacentre infrastructure and our HPC users. You will design, develop, test, configure, deploy and maintain the HPC user environment and engage with scientists, providing support and consultancy to enable them to make best use of our research infrastructure You perform activities aimed at ensuring high quality and performant implementations and adherence to standards within the teams of work you are part of. You participate into planning and review activities, collaborating with  colleagues, scientists, and other stakeholders for the necessary implementations and well as to communicate results."
	}
}

